All the documentation documents are in the docs folder in the root.
Read @development for previous context about development.
Read @CHANGELOG.md for context about current and ongoing changes.
Read @flow.md for development flow.
The development is API driven.
Check if Database is competent @openapi.yaml, if not implement migration -> Update OpenAPI -> Generate Types -> Create Backend -> Create Frontend Hooks -> Create Frontend UI -> Lint every file you have touched -> ask me to Test -> Write to Changelog

The project is extremely critical, and is massive. We will be implementing smaller features, first discuss, create to-do, then implement.
If you don't understand a thing, then please ask me and only THEN move forward. DO NOT be confused about anything. If you are confused, your responsibility is to ask ME.

Remember, lint every file you have touched using internal tools, deno check every backend file you have touched.

Never ever run the development server or the supabase functions serve command. Remember, they are always running (ran by me), you do not need to run them again.

We will ALWAYS work on this project incrementally. Feature by feature. We will break a feature down into its subcomponents, and only then will we work on every subcomponent slowly. We will tackle all problems systematically instead of rushing and implementing it in its entirety in one go.

ALWAYS follow @flow.md for development.
Flow describes a simple development process:
1. Check if DB is competent
2. If not, migrations
3. Decide upon backend, endpoints
4. Update OpenAPI as required
5. Implement backend work
6. Decide upon hooks and frontend
7. Implement frontend work
8. Implement UI work